history.content: yeah I know this isn't a EE/CS class but it is an elective, and I am trying to seek out a lower-workload class to balance my other 3 classes, all of which apparently are high workload.  I have nothing but technicals left. Anyone take this class in the last year and can comment on the workload amount?  From what I understand from last semester, there was no final and there were 10 programming projects/assignments in Python.  But there's a different lecturer this Fall.  Use DeNero 61A as the baseline. If you can specify number of hours spent per week outside of lecture/discussion, that would be awesome...TIA! (I very much prefer a project-based class as opposed to an exam-oriented class).  If it matters, I'm planning on taking STAT 140 and CS 61C, and maybe retake CS 61B (I took it in CC already).
